OL,3,CConclave: How is a new Pope elected?
OL,5,FThe historic vote, which often happens
OL,6,Fbetween 15 to 20 days after the Pope's
OL,7,Fdeath, is shrouded in secrecy.
OL,9,FWho can be pope?
OL,11,FAny baptised Catholic can be elected
OL,12,Fpope, but since 1379 every pope has
OL,13,Fbeen selected from the College of
OL,14,FCardinals - the group who cast the
OL,15,Fvotes at the conclave.
OL,17,FCardinals are senior members of the
OL,18,Fclergy, many who are bishops and
OL,19,Farchbishops appointed by the pope.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
