OL,3,CConclave: How is a new Pope elected?
OL,5,FThe rules of the conclave, as of
OL,6,FJanuary 22, 2025, stated there are 138
OL,7,Felectors - and therefore 138 eligible
OL,8,Fpapal candidates - of the 252
OL,9,Fcardinals.
OL,11,FOnly those under the age of 80 may
OL,12,Ftake part in the secret ballot.
OL,14,FHow does the vote take place?
OL,16,FOnce the cardinals have arrived, the
OL,17,Fconclave begins with a special morning
OL,18,FMass in St Peter's Basilica. In the
OL,19,Fafternoon, the cardinals walk to the
OL,20,FSistine Chapel to start the voting
OL,21,Fprocess.
