OL,3,CConclave: How is a new Pope elected?
OL,5,FThe College of Cardinals then take a
OL,6,Fvow of secrecy inside the chapel and,
OL,7,Fwith the exception of a few workers,
OL,8,Fno one else is allowed in.
OL,10,FAll communications with the outside
OL,11,Fworld, including phones and the
OL,12,Finternet, are removed and the chapel
OL,13,Fis checked for recording devices.
OL,15,FThe cardinals are handed voting papers
OL,16,Fto write the name of the person they
OL,17,Fhave selected.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
