OL,3,CConclave: How is a new Pope elected?
OL,5,FOne by one - in order of seniority -
OL,6,Fthey take it in turns to approach the
OL,7,Faltar where they leave it on a plate,
OL,8,Fpray, below the words "Eligo in Summun
OL,9,FPontificem" - Latin for "I elect as
OL,10,Fsupreme pontiff" - and then place it
OL,11,Fin an urn.
OL,13,FThe names are then counted and if a
OL,14,Fname has received two-thirds of the
OL,15,Fvotes, the pope has been elected.
OL,17,FIf the first ballot does not produce a
OL,18,Fresult, a maximum of four ballots are
OL,19,Fheld on each successive day: two in
OL,20,Feach morning and two in each afternoon.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
