OL,3,CConclave: How is a new Pope elected?
OL,5,FThe process is repeated for three
OL,6,Fdays, after which there is a day's
OL,7,Frest for prayer, reflection and
OL,8,Finformal discussions.
OL,10,FThe voting then begins again for a
OL,11,Fseries of seven more ballots and then
OL,12,Fanother break.
OL,14,FThe process is repeated twice more and
OL,15,Fif there is still a stalemate, the
OL,16,Fchamberlain will declare a result can
OL,17,Fcome from an absolute majority or by a
OL,18,Fvote on the two names that received
OL,19,Fthe largest number of votes in the
OL,20,Flast ballot.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
